commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, there are some check style and code quality issues.

Address these issues by refactoring the ScreenJobCommand logic from
comparing strings to using a predicate. In addition, resolve Javadocs
issues.

This refactor prepares ScreenCommand for future iterations where it
will be refactored to use generics.

This approach enhances the code structure without affecting
functionality, setting the stage for future improvements
while maintaining the current stability
and passing check style validation.

Currently, there is a bug in the code where if the user type
"screen 1" it will show a message stating that the index is missing,
which is not correct.

Address the issue by fixing the bug displaying the exception message.

This ensures that the appropriate exception message is shown.
